! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|v0.1.5 |2026-05-25 |''Cascade-palette: Manage kinds (edit existing type-defs).'' New `palette/` subfolder ships a cascade-palette entry "Manage kinds" (`đź§°`, order 130, grouped under Kind Actions) tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry`. Drilling lists every existing kind type-definition tiddler as a row (caption + icon resolved from `kind.caption` / `kind.icon`). Picking a kind drills to a metadata-edit stage with five text-edit rows â€” one per flat `kind.*` field (`caption`, `icon`, `namespaces`, `title-formula`, `stream-fields`) â€” bound directly to the type-def tiddler. Each row uses cascade-palette's `ca-kind: text` so Space enters edit mode, Enter commits the new value to the type-def. A confirm-wrapped ''đź—‘ Delete this kind'' leaf at the bottom removes the type-def tiddler (instances unaffected). ''Files:'' new `palette/cascade-helpers.tid` (wikitext function library mirroring the existing cascade-helpers' addprefix/addsuffix JSON-emission pattern â€” `kind.cascade-manage-kinds-items`, `kind.cascade-manage-kind-row`, `kind.cascade-kind-edit-items`, `kind.cascade-meta-row`, `kind.cascade-delete-kind-row`) and `palette/entries/manage-kinds.tid` (the root entry). Editing the per-field `kind.fields` JSON array stays in the existing type-builder tab for now â€” follow-up will add cascade-mode field-list editing. Pure tiddler changes â€” no JS, no restart. |
|v0.1.4 |2026-05-21 |Ships ''`scopes/instances-of.tid`'' â€” a cascade-palette scope tiddler tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/scope`''. Adds the `,` prefix so the user can type `,<kind>` to restrict any cascade-palette result list to instances of that kind (e.g. `,node` filters to `[tag[node]]`). Argument is a kind tiddler title. Pure tiddler change â€” no JS, no restart. Requires cascade-palette â‰Ą 0.0.25 for the scope strip mechanism. |
|v0.1.3 |2026-05-21 |All three root entries (`Find entity`, `Find by kind`, `Create entity`) now carry `ca-group: Kind Actions` so they cluster under a shared header in the cascade-palette root menu (when grouping is enabled) instead of falling back to the auto-derived plugin name "kind". Tiddler-only change. |
|v0.1.2 |2026-05-21 |''Cascade integration â€” drill-fixing pass.'' (a) Fixed `kind.is-editable-field` â€” was `:filter[function[kind.is-computed-typed],â€¦is[blank]]` which always evaluated to empty (`is[blank]` operates on titles, and is-computed-typed outputs `$title`/`$calculated` non-blank when matched), so every field was rejected as "not editable". Now uses `count[]match[0]` to keep fields where is-computed-typed produced zero rows. (b) `kind.save-leaf-build` rewritten â€” earlier version closed the JSON string with `\"}` (JSON-escaped quote = quote INSIDE the string, never closing it) AND emitted filter args as `"K","D"` (quoted strings are not a valid filter operand form). Now closes with `"}` and uses literal-bracket args `[K],[D]` (with brackets injected via the `_brackets` textref to dodge the parser's bracket counter). Same `\"}`â†’`"}` fix on `kind.kind-find-build` / `kind.kind-create-build`. (c) `kind.collection-build` now embeds `ca-bind-tiddler` + `ca-bind-field` so cascade-palette can render the currently-selected value on the right of single/multi-select picker drills (Parent etc.) â€” empty â†’ `(unset)`, single ref â†’ caption, multi â†’ comma-joined. (d) `kind.cascade-fields-for-create` split so `:map:flat[field-edit-items]` runs ONLY over the draft-tid, not over the save-leaf JSON (previous version mapped both, producing one empty result + skipping the actual field edits). New helper `kind.field-edit-items-for-draft`. (e) Single-select picker leaves (`kind.enum-leaf-one`, `kind.ref-leaf-build`) now emit `ca-after-fire: pop` â€” cascade-palette fires the action, pops the picker stage, keeps the palette open on the create-fields stage. Pure tiddler changes â€” no restart required. |
|v0.1.1 |2026-05-21 |Cascade-palette integration. Three new root entries: `Find entity` (cross-type search by caption+title), `Find by kind` (drill kinds â†’ instances), `Create entity` (in-palette draft + Save leaf). Three universal actions on any `kind.type`-tagged tiddler: `Open`, `Edit fields` (per-field menu with kind data-types: text/longtext/number/date/datetime/enum/ref), `Delete` (with confirm-drill). One palette template renders `view.tid` in the details drawer. All field synthesis runs through `cascade-helpers.tid` (~50 filter functions, no JS) |
|v0.1.0 |2026-05-20 |Initial release. One-tiddler-per-type schema model with namespacing; hand-rolled editor/creator/view/stream-view/validator/type-builder; field types text/longtext/number/date/datetime/enum/ref ($title and $calculated for computed values); constraints required/min/max/unique/unique:wiki; auto-computed titles via filter formula |
